title: Unirradiated melanocytes
treatment_protocol_ch1: A dose of irradiation was applied to quiescent melanocytes on day 1 and then again 24 hrs later.
growth_protocol_ch1: Cultured primary melanocytes were made quiescent prior to the exposure of solar UVR (UVA+UVB)
extract_protocol_ch1: By 64 hr post-irradiation, exosomes from the irradiated or un-irradiated melanocytes were subjected to RNA extraction using the Total Exosome RNA and Protein Kit (Invitrogen).
label_protocol_ch1: 130 ng of total RNA was labeled by using Affymetrix's Flash Tag Biotin HS RNA Labeling Kit.
hyb_protocol: For hybridization, Affymetrix GeneChip Hybridization Wash and Stain Kit was used.
scan_protocol: Chips were scanned with Affymetrix GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G.
description: miRNA expression data from non-irradiated melanocytes
data_processing: The CEL files were imported into the Affymetrix Expression Console Software for analysis and the generation of CHP files.  CHP files were analyzed using the Affymetrix Transcriptome Analysis Consol (TAC) software.
